Description: 100% authentic men's Omega Seamaster Professional Quartz Swiss Precision divers wristwatch offered on a $1 start no reserve auction! This is the watch that James Bond made famous in a number of films and it's the full size 41mm casing without crowns. This watch is reference 2541.80.00 and is Calibre 1538. The watch comes with it's original Omega inner red leather case with pillow and the original Omega white outer box as well. Both are in excellent condition. Along with the boxes are the original Omega hang tag specifying reference number, watch serial number and caliber number as well as all of the functions that the watch was designed with. Also has it's original Omega full size instructions book. Card set has never been opened! It's the 300 meter or 1000 feet water resistant Professional diver watch with the screw down Helium release crown. The unidirectional famous blue bezel is in fantastic condition and clicks 120 times per full turn. The sapphire crystal face is flawless and showcases the classic Seamaster blue wave dial which is in perfect condition. Both screw down crowns are perfectly operational with very quick date and hour setting available at position 2. Tritium luminosity is excellent. Bracelet is the full width of 20mm and it has the full length. Currently 3 and 1/2 are removed and can be added to bring it up to full length. The only superficial marks anywhere on the brilliant piece are on the back of the deployment clasp but these could be removed virtually by sneezing and you would have a watch difficult to pick in a line up from a brand new one! Case back is perfect and carries the famous Omega Hippocampus symbol against the wave patterned seabed. New battery fitted should go for 3 years! An absolutely stunning piece and these 41mm casing sizes are getting harder to find. 45mm including crown by the way :)) Bid with confidence and secure yourself an absolute bargain!
